NOTICE for ginx (Original Work):
================================================================================

This project (gint) is a derivative work based on ginx, with the following modifications:

1. Simplified architecture - Removed enterprise-level features for lightweight use
2. Redesigned session management - Implemented dual-token mechanism (Access Token + Refresh Token)
3. Enhanced validation system - Adopted design patterns (Strategy + Builder + Composite)
4. Added new features:
   - Unified response code system (0=success, 1=warning, 2=error)
   - Memory-based session provider for development/testing
   - Active connection limit middleware
   - Enhanced context with convenient parameter access
   - Support for regexp2 with advanced regex features

5. Documentation - Completely rewritten in Chinese for better accessibility

The original ginx project is Copyright by ecodeclub and contributors.
Original source: https://github.com/ecodeclub/ginx
Original license: Apache License 2.0

================================================================================

